title: Prince Charles’ Aussie birthday BBQ
text:
A BBQ, charity and a museum: Inside Prince Charles and Camilla’s Aussie itinerary Wires News Corp Australia Network A BBQ, charity and a museum: Inside Prince Charles and Camilla’s Aussie itinerary Wires News Corp Australia Network Packed schedule ... Prince Charles and his wife Camilla will be in Australia next month. Picture: AFP 
PRINCE Charles and his wife Camilla will celebrate his birthday at a beachside barbecue in Perth during his 15th visit to Australia next month. 
The royal couple on Tuesday announced a 12-day tour of Australia and New Zealand from November 4-15. 
Their trip will take in Sydney, Canberra, Adelaide, Perth and Albany where they will mark the centenary of Gallipoli by visiting the new National Anzac Centre to view the point from which troop convoys departed. Aussie trip ... Prince Charles and Camilla will spend nearly two weeks Down Under. Picture: Images Getty 
The royal couple will also get a taste of regional life in the South Australian town of Tanunda and celebrate the Prince’s birthday with West Australian families at a barbecue at Cottesloe Beach in Perth. 
In Sydney the Duchess of Cornwall will visit the Oz Harvest, a charity which collects surplus food and redistributes it to charities which support the vulnerable. Aussie style ... the royals have been frequent visitors to Aussie shores, with the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge (pictured in Katoomba) here last year. Picture: Splash 
The prince will also visit the National Museum in Canberra and in Perth hear about the efforts of the Western Australian Seed Technology Centre to preserve Western Australia’s biodiversity. The couple will spend Remembrance Day in Canberra where he will meet Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull and attend the National Ceremony at the Australian War Memorial. Other Stories
